(7, 1, 1, 'Cap1', 6, '', 1229758940, 'Salaams everyone! This is a great initiative Abbas sir and hope we get good representation from experts and users across Pakistan. I''m a Karachi-based practical newbie to guns so will be counting on everyone''s guidance in all things big or small. Happy & safe shooting! :cool:', 0, 1, '202.70.151.213', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2, 8),
(9, 4, 0, 'Cap1', 6, '', 1229761586, 'Hi guys. In your experience, what''s the best way to conceal carry a pistol if wearing trousers/jeans with no jacket? Average built person. What are the recommended good holsters available in Karachi?\n\nDo I need to carry the license also? Original or copy? BTW I''ve heard some mixed opinions but most people (including a CPLC guy) told me an all Pakistan license issued by Ministry of Interior Islamabad allows concealed carry, but not display. It mentions on pg 5 [i]"Licence for the possession of arms and ammunition [b][u]and for going armed[/u][/b] for the purposes of protection".[/i]', 0, 1, '202.70.151.213', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 5, 10),
(10, 1, 1, 'Hunter', 7, '', 1229764284, 'hi my name is hamid i am from kohat . i love hunting and guns i want to thank abbas  for his effort and for starting this great website keep up the good work', 0, 1, '58.65.203.51', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2, 11),
(13, 4, 9, 'Abbas', 1, '', 1229782918, 'As advice I would not recommend that you carry your weapon on your person unless there is a real threat to your security. \n\nIt is subject to debate but it''s mostly illegal to carry a concealed weapon. The line you are quoting from the license (pg 5) is a general description of the usage of the license. If you look at page 29 of the same license first para, it says "he shall not take any such arms to a fair, religious procession or place of public assemblage". Any place where people are gathered (Parks, Markets, Offices, Restaurants etc even a bus) is classified as a place of public assemblage. Hence your taking the weapon there even with a license become illegal. \n\nBut all those are technicalities, the point is, Don''t carry your weapon on your person unless you *NEED* to.\n \n\nAs far the ways to conceal a weapon without wearing a jacket. There are three popular ways.\n\n1). Ankle Holster [img]http://www.uncle-mikes.com/images/ankle_holster.jpg[/img]\n\n2). Pocket Holster [img]http://www.uncle-mikes.com/images/inside_pocket_holster.jpg[/img]\n\n3). Belt Holster [img]http://www.uncle-mikes.com/images/side_bet.jpg[/img]\n\nAll of the above holsters are made by Uncle Mike''s which is in my opinion the best Holster making company in the world. They are available in the local market from Rs. 2000 - Rs. 5000.', 0, 1, '117.102.51.27', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 5, 14),
(15, 6, 0, 'Abbas', 1, '', 1229783780, 'Hi, \n\nI put up this website and forum in a hurry as I didn''t have much time to spare. Please add your suggestions/comments for improving the website. \n\nI''m also looking for website/graphic designers with some spare time to contribute. This is a free site for everyone''s benefit.\n\n\nThanks.', 0, 1, '117.102.51.27', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 7, 17),
(22, 4, 9, 'Cap1', 6, '', 1229861581, 'Thanks for the good advice Abbas sir. Yes I don''t intend to carry the weapon most of the time.', 0, 1, '202.70.154.118', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 5, 24),
(24, 7, 0, 'Abbas', 1, 'How to Transport your Guns by Air (Legally ofcouse!)', 1229979819, 'Hi,\n\nI travel quite a bit within the country and prefer to carry a weapon with me from time to time. Since I do all my purchasing here in Lahore I also sometimes need to carry weapons for my security staff in other cities. Most people I meet are quite surprised to find that I am able to carry weapons so casually in this day and age with so many airport security checks. I''m surprised at the fact, how can you not ??  If your weapon is legal and you are the license holder, it''s TOTALLY LEGAL to transport your weapon to other cities (provided you have a all Pakistan license).\n\nHere the procedure. When you enter the airport (not the drive in/parking, the main door)  before you place your bag with the weapon in the scanning machine, tell the security person there that you are transporting your weapon and its in your bag. He''ll ask for your license. Show your license and a copy of your ID card. You''ll have to show him your gun, he''ll compare the gun number with the license, enter it in a register, enter your ID card info along with your flight information and ask you for your signature. Once that''s done, lock the bag and he''ll accompany you to the plastic wrap machine, get your bag sealed (free of cost) and then accompany you and the bag to the flight check in desk and oversee you check in the locked bag with the gun. That''s it, just pick up your bag normally from the baggage line when you reach and you''re done!\n\nI''ve even gone so far as to transport gun boxes without bags and pick them up from the baggage lines although it''s fun to see people''s expressions at the baggage line seeing guns next to their bags :lol:', 0, 1, '117.102.5.174', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 8, 26),
(27, 8, 0, 'Abbas', 1, '', 1229981125, 'I would like to start of with a review of P.A.R.A arms located in Bank Square, Anarkali. Lahore.\n\nI and my family have dealt with these guys for a quite some time, bought 50 plus weapons in total. They have a decent amount of variety and prices are fair. The better thing that I like about them is that I''ve never heard of them doing any "2" number things. It''s run by an very pleasant ex army man and his staff is knowledgeable and decent.  \n\nPhone numbers are: 7231167 and 7357143.', 0, 1, '117.102.5.174', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 9, 29),
(29, 10, 0, 'Abbas', 1, 'Review: Viper Pump Action Shotgun (Turkish)', 1229988826, 'Salams,\n\nI bought two .12 gague Vipers recently and tested them throughly. It is an excellent gun. Firing it reminds me of the Winchester Defender 1300. I think they tried to copy that design and did a fairly good job. Realibilty/durability seems good. As a mini test, I fired a box of 25 continuously only waiting for reloads. The barrel kept at a reasonable temperature and the entire box fired without a single jam.\n\nIt is a 5 + 1. The box includes an original pistol grip and the attached stock is simply beautiful. Highly recommended. I wish I bought more ! :)\n\nMy buying price was Rs. 25,000. Current price is around 30 K.', 0, 1, '117.102.5.174', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 12, 32),
(31, 7, 24, 'Cap1', 6, '', 1230002236, 'Thanks Abbas sir this is useful info as always. Is it easy to buy a pistol in a different city and get it registered with the DCO back home? I don''t see any reason why not. I don''t suppose the ASF guys would also want to see the DCO''s registration on the license?', 0, 1, '202.70.154.86', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 8, 34),
(33, 7, 24, 'Abbas', 1, '', 1230024942, 'Np, you can buy a gun anywhere within Pakistan from a Genuine Registered Firearms dealer. DCO registration is from your city of residence.\n\nAnyone who checks a license almost always looks at three things. Your Info, Bank Stamp and DCO stamp. \n\nAnother thing that skips people''s attention and causes them problems later on is that when you purchase a weapon you have to get it registered at the DCO office within 30 days. Most people don''t know that or take longer. Without the DCO stamp your weapon is not fully legal/complete.', 0, 1, '117.102.5.174', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 8, 36),
