(49, 10, 29, 'Abbas', 1, '', 1230459809, 'Salams guys, I tried to find any web sites / pictures on the Viper but didn''t come up with much. Here are the pictures that you asked for Balazona. I have two of these, this is a packaged/greased piece. The other piece is in use in Karachi.  \n\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Viper1.jpg[/img]\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Viper2.jpg[/img]\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Viper3.jpg[/img]\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Viper4.jpg[/img]\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Viper5.jpg[/img]\n\n\nHope you liked it! I didn''t put it together because I would have to take off the plastic restricter inside the chamber and ungrease it and I would like keep it greased till the time I need it. If I remember I''ll take some snaps of the other piece in Karachi which is in use on my next trip and post. \n\n@Cap1 You can most defiantly use the same shotgun for both hunting and home defense purposes. For home use the pistol grip is much more convenient / maneuverable and the for hunting the long stock is more accurate.\n\nShotguns are a tough bunch, people used to saw off half the barrel to make it more transportable and for close combat.', 0, 1, '117.102.5.174', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 12, 52),
(50, 11, 40, 'Abbas', 1, '', 1230460500, 'Hi BlackCloak,\n\nHe''s right, the retainer does not have the right to fire the weapon, he can only keep it in safe custody for the original owner. \n\nThe info about the firms being issued license is also accurate.', 0, 1, '117.102.5.174', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 13, 53),
