(100, 1, 1, 'Wampyr', 21, '', 1230722264, '[Safety On]\n\nAOA guys, I am Wampyr from Rawalpindi. During NCC, I got 10/10 in 100 meter shooting. It was some (don''t remember exact rifle name) semi-automatic American made rifle. From that day I realize I am natural with guns :D (because most of my friends were getting 0/10 or 1/10 and were unable to even position or aim gun properly).\n\nI have just general knowledge about guns. My father never let me buy any gun. However, now I am thinking of buying an average pistol and maybe a pump-action shotgun. But the curve to get a license always refrain me from any progress. I don''t have that much [i]contacts[/i].\n\nI''ll hang out here to get more knowledge and have good time with you guys :)\n\nAllah Hafiz', 0, 1, '58.27.144.110', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2, 104),
(101, 6, 15, 'Wampyr', 21, '', 1230722465, '[quote=Abbas]As far as the test site that you sent me. It was good![/quote]\nGlad to hear that.\n\n[quote=Abbas]I really liked the flash part, that is a fantastic idea and looks excellent. Since I want to stick with the current layout for a while I''ve been trying to visualize where we could fit a proper version of that animation in the current site without making the webpage slow. The only place it would fit and look good is if we make the logo part of the animation. As soon as the page loads, the normal ''two pistols'' logo displays for 5 seconds and then the flash animation starts from there and runs about 5 guns like you made it and ends at the logo again.\n\nHow can we make that happen while keeping the size small ?[/quote]\n\nThat''s a nice idea. I''ll try to make that flash animation. Let''s see what will be the out-come.', 0, 1, '58.27.144.110', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 7, 105),
(103, 12, 45, 'Cap1', 6, '', 1230744700, 'Welcome muzzogr8! I''m from Karachi. I''ve been trying to get access to a range myself but what with the internal and external situation I''m told to wait for now. I heard (not verified yet) that Karsaz is not allowing new civilian members at this time.\nTrust me I''m no expert so I can only tell you to follow the discussions here to learn from the [u]real[/u] gurus on choosing your first weapon. I recently got my first licence and got a Chinese Norinco NP-42 pistol 9MM following their advise. \nThese are the steps I went through:\n1. Go to an arms dealer (preferably a reputable one with some friend who knows them) and ask the process for All Pakistan, Non-Prohibited Bore (NPB) license. I went to Lucky Star area.\n2. Once you have the license, get it endorsed at National Bank Main Branch, I.I. Chundrigar Rd, ASAP within a month of issue date\n3. You have six months from the issue date to get your weapon & DCO registration\n4. Buy a weapon, try to test fire it before the next steps just in case (slim chance) there is some problem and you need to go back to the shop. Keep a couple of spent shells. No firing range access means [i]hawai firing [/i]i guess; thats what I had to do but felt very bad disturbing the neighborhood :/\n5. Take the license, original purchase receipt (keep copies for your record), license copy and CNIC copy to DCO office (right opp Karachi Gymkhana) for registration. Try and get it done the same day but from what I saw they asked to leave it and come collect it ''tomorrow''. I got it the next day.\n6. Go to your local police station with the license, a copy of it, copy of CNIC, one photo and the two shells and they will register your weapon. It just took me 10 minutes. \nDo get some ear protection when firing and use safety glasses when firing or cleaning the gun.\nAll done! Happy & safe shooting.', 0, 1, '202.70.149.57', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 14, 107),
