(288, 44, 281, 'Abbas', 1, '', 1231271452, 'I''m a fan of the GSG 5. It''s a great little gun and the way it looks is worth the money, specially the one that comes with the silencer lookalike barrel cover. \n\n.22 generally don''t have any practical defense usage but as you said, they are some of the most fun weapons to use. Good on the range, good for Rabbits etc with a scope. A shotgun blows the little things to bits and the smaller pellets become a pain in the backside to get rid off once cleaning the animal. \n\nBullets are cheap as well. I wonder if the GSG can fire .22 magnums. If it can, those can be lethal.\n\nSomeone was telling me the other day that the security detail of the U.S President carry .22 handguns for accuracy. Any comments ?', 0, 1, '117.102.5.174', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 58, 366),
(291, 18, 105, 'Taurus', 24, '', 1231273160, 'HYE ABBAS CONGRATS 4 buying such beautiful pistols MASHALLAH i am really happy:) u got gr8 pistol of the world..abbas bhai does glock have more barrel life,how much is the barrel life approximately?Congrats', 0, 1, '58.27.148.176', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 22, 369),
(293, 18, 105, 'Abbas', 1, '', 1231274896, 'Thanks everyone. \n\nBarrel life depends on how you use your pistol. If you fire one round per 10 sec, the barrel life would be different, one round per second means less barrel life than one in 10 sec, and on auto even lesser. \n\nBut, regardless I have not heard of anyone wearing a Glock barrel out from too much use. There are Glocks out there have 50,000 + rounds put through them and still going strong. The Beretta 92 FS''s are great in that department as well, reports of 100,000 plus on the orginal barrel. The barrels generally last till the pistol itself and Glocks are built tough. \n\nBtw even if the barrel gets worn out that doesn''t mean the pistol will misfire or jam, the worst case scenario is that it starts to become inaccurate.', 0, 1, '117.102.5.174', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 22, 373),
