(538, 64, 0, 'MAH', 51, '', 1231570055, 'Given members knowledge I want to find out what ammo works best with with different pistols. I''ll share my experiences\n\nFor 0.22 lr, in my experience the best was American Egale/Federal and CCI brands, no failure to fire, or eject - this was using the Ruger, Walther, S&W Revolver and Sif Mosquito.\n\nAt the Gun Club range a few months back I tried the Chinese 9mm rounds (they come in either blue or red boxes, there may be others), and I had a terrible experience. I was shooting with a bunch of friends and between us we had Glock 26, PT 92 and QZ-75 (essentially a Chinese copy of CZ-75). Well for every ten rounds we shot on the Chinese Ammo, we had aleast one failure to fire. QZ-75 even had a failure to feed the round properly. As compared to the Chinese Ammo, POF rounds shot much better and since then most of the people that I know prefer to use POF rounds. \n\nCan other members share their experience with ammo (with different types of weapons) as well.\n\nCheers', 0, 1, '203.99.191.138', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 88, 714),
