(645, 6, 15, 'OHQ', 25, '', 1231685817, '[quote=Abbas]The online store thing sounds like a good idea. I''ll start working on it when we cross 100 forum users InshAllah.[/quote]\n\nOne thing I have noticed that arms dealer don’t have cleaning kits rest you can get bullets, guns I went through a couple of good web sites the best and oldest one was Hoppes. They have some good stuff. I was thinking that Cap1 suggested online store and Abbas bhai said after 100 members have joined the forum by this speed we will be there by next month. Why not import some cleaning kits and put them on our online store and maybe somthing else. Members any Idea''s? I hope that’s legal.  Which brand or which kit to go for we can always open a new topic and have a discussion on it.', 0, 1, '115.186.96.49', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 7, 848),
(646, 1, 1, 'Ahmad', 54, '', 1231691519, 'AOA\nto all members,my name is Mashhood Ahmad & live in Multan. i am very happy to see a website of our country on guns. i used to read on  many Gun forums,  and always thought that we should have one here. \nHope to share & learn from fellow members.', 0, 1, '116.71.153.120', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2, 854),
(647, 33, 210, 'Ahmad', 54, '', 1231692478, 'here is the current list of guns i got at the moment\n\nHand Guns\n\nColt SAA Army 1st Generation 45 LC \nColt Official Police Positive 5" barrel 38 special\nS&W Victory Model Revolver 38 Special\nIthaca 1911A1 45 ACP\nLuger 9MM\nCZ 52 7.62 x 25\nNorinco 213 (TT variant 9MM)\n\nRifles/Shotgun\n\nWinchester defender 1300\nR B Roda SxS external hammer\nErma 22 Rifle\nAK 101 (5.56x45)\ntoday traded my Adler .22 mag for an old 22 LR (Beretta 1934 model) i was facing some problem in MAG so i sold it out, the dealer happened to bought that old rifle same day so i bought it to cover license until i find some other 22 mag\nthanks', 0, 1, '116.71.153.120', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 43, 856),
(648, 34, 211, 'Ahmad', 54, '', 1231692970, 'the ammo for SMG is marked MK2 ( in roman digits) and for pistol it is marked MK1, so always look on the box for proper marking. yes it is leaves quite a residue and i happened to see a lot of duds or misfire in POF ammo.\nregards', 0, 1, '116.71.153.120', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 44, 858),
