(727, 67, 575, 'Bored2676', 13, '', 1231771984, '[quote=Acciprone]btw... this dealer i visited told me yesterday that he will be importing this gun.. which is an exact replica of a glock .. apparently they are so good side by side u could not make out the difference.. he should have it in 15 day... ill go and check it out. and let u guys know[/quote]\n\nI have bought a 92Fs replica and from the outside it is indistinguishable.  Even the barrel is quite good.  However, if you take the pistol apart, you can tell it was hand made in "kharad" fashion.  So far the barrel has not exploded so it gives me hope but I will still not trust my life to it.\n\nI bought it one from of the guys who is actually supplying your dealers (as far as I know, there are two guys who make nearly perfect copies, the rest are the "do nambars" of the do nambar trade :) they have recently moved their business from Dara Adamkhel to Peshawer).  I went to this guy 6 months ago and at that time, he told me that he is developing copies of Glock as well as S&W guns which will be perfect.  So I saw some of the initial versions which were quite good but you could tell the difference.  I am still not confident on their abilities where polymer is concerned.  I suppose I will drop by the factory to check it out when I get the time.', 0, 1, '203.82.55.89', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 93, 979),
(729, 35, 212, 'Bored2676', 13, '', 1231772679, 'Well.......in Pakistan, that is the general approach.  But let me boil it down for you:\n\nSolvents dissolve powder residue and dirt. WD-40 is an average solvent. \nLubricants make the gun function smoother. WD-40 is an average lubricant.\nRust protectants protect the gun from rust. WD-40 is an average protectant.\n\nIt is basically the jack of all trades and master of none. \n\nWD-40 is known to get gummy as the solvent/carrier evaporates over time as well as harden. WD40 is not only a *lubricant* but an effective *penetrant* (read the label). It is the penetrant properties that are damaging. While these work well in removing rust and corrosion, they can be *devastating* to well kept metal surfaces.  Also, as penetrant, a small quantity of WD on bullets can neutralize the primers. Test this by putting a few WD40 coated rounds in a zip lock bag for a week. You''re bound to get one or two "sizzlers" at the end of that time.\n\nIf you are going to use it, I would suggest to use it on the outside of the gun, not on the inside.\n\nPowder solvent is nitro powder solvent.  The common one available in Pakistan is hoppes.  Its generally used inside the barrel.', 0, 1, '203.82.55.89', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 45, 981),
