(1027, 78, 885, 'Firepower!', 16, '', 1231998980, 'The Pakistani Beretta is a hit or miss deal. One my secretaries has it. It works fine. The one that the house keeper has is just ok. Then I have seen ones which really fall apart after a few magazines of fire. \n\nThe finishing is better on the SS versions, they cost a little more as well. If you take it apart the parts inside are rough. They are proclivity to get rusted sooner than one would think. \n\nThe QA is a big issue with them. Do not have consistancy at all. I dont recommend them as of yet since every specimen varies of quality. \n\nGun should never be just to look at until its an antique.', 0, 1, '58.65.153.159', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 111, 1403),
