(1066, 45, 306, '9mm Luger', 66, '', 1232015030, 'AOA,\n\nI am a new member from Karachi and I own a 24/7 pro in 9mm. i have fed federal and wolf (russian) bullets to my baby with no problem.. actually one of my freind who owns the same toy tried using the wolf and had a jam/FTE every second round so gave me some round to get them checked... all i can say is that its better to use american bullet if you want a long life for your pistol.. POF and WOLF both leave a very high residue and do damage the finish..unless your an avid cleaner and will clean out the gun as soon as you have finished firing...chinese..hmm..never tried them\n\nMy friend switched to POF and is now satisfied with the Taurus except that he complains of the high residue left behind (which is the problem with the bullets not the pistol!!).. one thing i would like to mention is that a lot of newbies (even like me when i started off) use a lot of oil when cleaning our pistols!! and from experinence i have come to know that running oil always create a problem !! i always wipe my gun clean of any excess before i shoot or take out for a carry!', 0, 1, '221.120.203.122', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 60, 1447),
