(2132, 138, 0, 'Abbas', 1, '', 1232915418, 'Salams, There are other threads dedicated to firing ranges in Islamabad/Pindi and for Karachi but none for Lahore. I thought since no other member has yet chipped in I would contribute my two cents.\n\nThere are two firing ranges in Lahore that I know of, one is called the Lahore Rifle Club. It is located on Shami Road in Cantt, just before the Battle Axe Shell petrol station. The range is for small arms only and is a no frills sort of affair. There are about 40 lanes, targets are free and get changed on request. 25 M as well as 50 M targets are available. The only facility on offer is ear protectors and you need them at that range as the sound really echo''s there. I like it, it''s a nice clean range. Membership fee is [B]Rs. 24,000 and Rs. 1,000 / month.[/B]\n\nThe name of the range master is Faisal Azad and his contact number is 0321-9422297.\n\nThe other range that I know of  is located at the Garrison Golf Club near the new airport. It is for .12 gauge and for skeet shooting only. I don''t know many details about it yet. (On last update, it has been closed)\n\nBtw both ranges are Saturday and Sunday only.', 0, 1, '115.186.96.191', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 195, 2746),
