(2139, 12, 45, 'Cap1', 6, '', 1232936033, 'Salaams guys. I''m in the process myself. This is my experience with the police certificate:\n* I went to TPO office TIB section, showed them the PN form and they stamped on the back referring to my local PS\n* Local PS didn''t tell me the requirements in one go, but ultimately they wanted my CNIC copy plus 2 photos and CNICs copies of two other people from my area (not relatives). \n* The local PS guys wrote out a statement ''bayan'' for me to sign stating that I live at this address, I want PN membership just for training and practice and I have no connections with organized groups. \n* Local PS also wrote out statements for my two friends to sign saying that they knew me for so many years and I was not involved in any wrong activities or court proceedings. Better to take them along to save time, I had to take the forms and go get them signed by my friends.\n* Local PS then processed the documents and sent them to DSP (based out of yet another PS). I went the next day and they gave me the processed docs to take back to the TPO. I kept copies for my record.\n* The TPO kept all the documents and I got the final certificate after 2 days from them. The certificate is a separate letter addressed to the PN referring to their letter # and saying that I am resident at this address for so many years and there''s no adverse record about me. The TPO kept the PN letter in their record.\nAll in all about 5 days.', 0, 1, '58.181.107.156', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 14, 2756),
